grep -o "search" file | wc -l                            - count of occurrences 
grep "search" file | sort | uniq -c                    - count of each unique occurrence 
grep "search" file | sort | uniq -c | sort -n       - count of each unique occurrence asc
grep "search" file | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn      - count of each unique occurrence desc
grep -A 10...                                                  - grabs 10 lines after search
grep -B 10...                                                  - grabs 10 lines before search
grep -C 10...                                                  - grabs 10 lines before and after search

Input "/" while in a less command to search in file. 

(By Josh Hauser)
